	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Note:  This info is based on what I have experienced from being in a group with a shamen.<BR>
<BR>
Which are the two best classes to have in a group?  Bards, and SHAMANs.<BR>
<BR>
Friends take my advice, you have never been 'buffed' until you've been buffed by a shaman.  They have spells that will raise every single attribute that you have, plus spells that make you run faster, fight harder, and heal faster.  They are decent fighters (at low level before anyone can afford decent armor they are as good or better in combat then a cleric), and they have excellent physical stats because of the races that they have to choose from.<BR>
Far to often the Shaman class is overlooked by those trying to create a new and different character.<BR>
But then thats just my opinion...I could be wrong.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
